      "content": "a \"security test\"? if the press finds out we weren't actually testing anything and it was just an accidental mistake, they'll eat us alive for lying. it'll look way worse than just being sloppy. \n\ncan we go even further? like, can we characterize this as a routine system update or some kind of data synchronization process that just had some minor metadata discrepancies? i need something that completely moves the conversation away from \"security failure\" and makes it look like business as usual.",
